@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <h1 class="mb-4"><i class="bi bi-shield-lock-fill me-2"></i> Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>At <strong>RideRental</strong>, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our website and services.</p>

    <hr />

    <h5>1. Information We Collect</h5>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account Details:</strong> Full Name, Age, Occupation, Email, and Password.</li>
        <li><strong>Rental Information:</strong> Bike rental history, rental time, duration, and preferences.</li>
        <li><strong>License Upload:</strong> Images uploaded during registration for identification.</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>2. How We Use Your Information</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>To manage your bookings and bike rentals.</li>
        <li>To personalize bike recommendations and enhance your experience.</li>
        <li>To verify your identity and ensure compliance with safety policies.</li>
        <li>To communicate updates, offers, or system notifications.</li>
    </ul>

    <h5>3. Data Security</h5>
    <p>We implement robust security measures to protect your personal data. Passwords are stored securely, and all uploads are handled with care. Your data is never shared with third parties without your consent.</p>

    <h5>4. Cookies</h5>
    <p>Our site may use cookies to enhance your browsing experience. You can choose to disable cookies in your browser settings.</p>

    <h5>5. Your Rights</h5>
    <p>You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal data. To make changes, please contact our support team at <a href="mailto:admin@riderental.com">admin@riderental.com</a>.</p>

    <h5>6. Updates to This Policy</h5>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. All changes will be posted on this page with a revised date.</p>

    <hr />
    <p class="text-muted small">Last updated: @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</p>
</div>
